APPENDIX B: FIGURE CAPTIONS
Figure 1 (6-panel plot):
(Top Left) Overmassiveness Test: Black hole mass vs stellar mass for BCGs (red) and field galaxies (blue). BCGs are systematically offset above the field population, indicating overmassiveness. Dashed lines show M_BH/M_* = 0.2% (field average) and 2.0%.
(Top Middle) Power Law Fit: M_BH/M_* ratio vs cluster mass for 14 BCGs. Red dashed line shows best-fit power law M_BH/M_* ‚àù M_cluster^1.67. Despite scatter, there is a clear monotonic trend (Spearman œÅ=0.83, p=0.0002).
(Top Right) Direct M_BH-M_cluster Scaling: Black hole mass vs cluster mass. Purple dashed line shows M_BH ‚àù M_cluster^2.25, steeper than cooling flow prediction (Œ±=1.3, black dotted).
(Bottom Left) Stellar Mass Scaling: Stellar mass vs cluster mass for BCGs. Green dashed line shows M_* ‚àù M_cluster^0.58. Gray band shows theoretical expectation (0.5-0.8). Poor correlation (R¬≤=0.27) indicates heterogeneous measurements.
(Bottom Middle) Residuals: Scatter around the M_BH/M_* power-law fit. RMS residual = 0.28 dex indicates substantial scatter, likely from measurement heterogeneity.
(Bottom Right) Universal M_BH-M_DM Relation: Black hole mass vs total dark matter mass for BCGs (red, using M_cluster) and field galaxies (blue, using M_halo). Both populations follow a unified relation M_BH ‚àù M_DM^0.67 (black dashed), supporting a fundamental black hole-dark matter connection.

