   - Gets you a citable DOI (Digital Object Identifier)

2. **Credibility for Science Fairs** üèÜ
   - Judges are MORE impressed if you say: "My work is published on arXiv (arxiv.org/abs/2026.xxxxx)"
   - Shows you're doing "real science" not just a school project
   - Separates you from 99% of other science fair projects

3. **Gets Feedback BEFORE Judging** üí¨
   - Real astronomers might read it and comment
   - You can fix errors BEFORE presenting
   - Might even get an email from a professor offering collaboration!

4. **No Deadline Pressure** ‚è∞
   - Science fairs have hard deadlines
   - arXiv is rolling - submit anytime
   - Better to get it out early

5. **Required for Some Competitions** üìã
   - Some international fairs (ISEF-level) prefer or require prior publication
   - ArXiv counts as "published" for this purpose

